    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus. This example is equipped with the desirable G96 six-speed manual transaxle, ensuring tactile gear selection and mechanical longevity. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a rear main seal replacement. The suspension geometry is maintained via refreshed Bilstein dampers, providing excellent lateral stability and turn-in response. The Bosch Motronic engine management ensures a smooth power band, while the braking system retains firm pedal feel through four-piston monobloc calipers. Though the exterior shows minor evidence of high-speed aerodynamics, the drivetrain is robust and the chassis remains rigid. A precision-engineered driver's car ready for the canyon roads.",
